  "source": "Numerics/Test_Numerics/Distributions/Bivariate Copulas/Test_StudentTCopula.cs",
  "reference": "Test_StudentTCopula.cs is almost entirely qualitative (range/sign/ordering assertions against R 'copula' tCopula/dCopula/pCopula, not fixed literals) -- see the C# file's own header remark. Every numeric expected value in THIS fixture is therefore curated via oracle_emitter --dump (see fixtures/README.md), not transcribed from a C# test literal; every assertion below carries an explicit 'source' note. No fit oracles: the upstream Test_MPL_Fit/Test_IFM_Fit/Test_MPL_EstimatesBothParameters/Test_IFM_EstimatesBothParameters tests assert only ranges (e.g. 'rho should be > 0.5 and < 1.0'), not point estimates, so there is nothing fixed to transcribe or curate for fit cases.",
  "note": "pdf/cdf grid spans 10 (rho, nu) combinations (positive/negative rho, small/large nu) at the fixed point (0.3, 0.7), all at tight tolerance since the copula's CDF path (StudentT.InverseCDF -> MultivariateStudentT.CDF, a deterministic K=200 stratified chi-squared(v) mixture over the deterministic dim-2 MultivariateNormal.bivariate_cdf) has no seeded/statistical component. Tail dependence and inverse_cdf spot values are likewise curated. parameters_valid cases cover: a normal in-range pair, both rho bounds (theta=-2/+2 rejected regardless of df), and an out-of-range df via the IEEE df='inf' sentinel (isinf(nu) => invalid; NaN is intentionally NOT used here -- see student_t_copula.hpp's file-header fidelity note on std::max/Math.Max NaN-handling divergence in the SetCopulaParameters clamp). dof_clamp exercises SetCopulaParameters's own nu clamp (Math.Max(2.0 + 1E-10, parameters[1])) directly via the generic construct path.",
